	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1" facs="EHRI-ET-WL05320102_01.jpg"/>
			<p>Protocol No. 102</p>
			<p><date when="1940-01-02">2 January 1940</date></p>
			<p><persName ref="#ehri_et_r_avrom">Avrom R.</persName></p>
			<p>20-years old</p>
			<p>Harvester from <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/766027/lomza.html">Łomża</placeName></p>
			<p>Now – <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/593116/vilnius.html">Vilnius</placeName></p>

			<p>From <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">German</term> airplanes during 2 bombardments on the eve of Rosh Hashanah in <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/766027/lomza.html">Łomża</placeName>, <persName ref="#ehri_et_markevitsh">Markevitsh</persName> was
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-536" type="subject">killed</term> – a writer in the <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/766027/lomza.html">city hall</placeName>.</p>
			<p>I was detained by the <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Germans</term> in a <placeName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-1178" type="camp">prison camp close to Rastenburg [Kętrzyn]</placeName>.
				There were 13 hundred Jews there. They did not give us <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832"
					type="subject">food</term>. Every evening, they gave one loaf of <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">bread</term> to be shared by 4 persons, and this was
				all we had to <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">eat</term>.</p>
			<p>Once <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_poles">Polish</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-669" type="subject">prisoners</term> arrived. The <term
					ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Germans</term> ordered them to take off all our <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-836" type="subject">clothes</term>. They indeed undressed us until we were
				naked and took all of it for themselves.</p>
			<p>During my time in the <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-1178" type="camp">camp</placeName> – 3 weeks
				–, 3 <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-536" type="subject">Jews died</term> who could not endure the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-569" type="subject">hunger</term>, the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-831" type="subject">cold</term> and the beatings anymore.</p>
			<p>On the second day of Sukkot, a thousand <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826" type="subject">men</term>
				were released from the <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-1178" type="camp">camp</placeName> who were
				ordered to go to the <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_soviets">Soviet</term> territories. I was also released. <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/766027/lomza.html">Łomża</placeName> was transferred to the <term
					ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_soviets">Soviets</term>.</p>
			<p>I left for <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/593116/vilnius.html">Vilnius</placeName> because I have a <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">brother</term> in America and I want to go to him.</p>
			<p>Signed: <persName ref="#ehri_et_r_avrom">Avrom R.</persName></p>
		</body>
	</text>
